                <td colspan="6">
                  <p class="ia-table-text"><b>Other key non-monetised costs by ‘main affected groups </b></p>
                  <p class="ia-table-text">Under this option, the costs that are currently incurred by providers of schemes whose members wish to transfer, convert or otherwise flexibly access safeguarded-flexible benefits will continue.  The main costs are in valuing the associated guarantees, which may require actuarial support, and then checking that members have taken financial advice. The costs of valuing safeguarded-flexible benefits, particularly those that offer the member option of a Guaranteed Annuity Rates (GARs) have been higher than was originally anticipated as the complexity of applying the valuation method set in regulation was not foreseen. Therefore the full extent of these on-going costs was not accounted for in the original Impact Assessment<authorialNote marker="2"><p class="ia-table-text"> Amendments to Pension Schemes Bill (private sector defined benefit transfers) IA No: RPC14-HMT-2212 http://www.parliament.uk/documents/impact-assessments/IA14-13A.pdf</p></authorialNote>.  Under the Do Nothing option, these costs will continue in the future and will represent the baseline against which the costs and benefits of other options are assessed. As such, these costs have not been specifically quantified.</p>
