                  <p class="ia-table-text">Individuals who have safeguarded-flexible benefits worth more than £30,000 (when calculated as currently on the basis of the amount required to provide for the member’s benefits), but with a transfer value of less than £30,000 will no longer be required to pay for financial advice (from an adviser authorised by the Financial Conduct Authority) before proceeding to transfer or flexibly access their pension benefits; estimated maximum savings are £5.56m in the first year and £11.12m in subsequent years.</p>
